    "summary": "Vote NOW: capture decisions while fresh, revise later",
    "content": "NOW — The terminological decisions, convention debates, and philosophical rationales behind our translation choices are at their sharpest right now. We've just been through intensive deliberation on the 德 split, the 现象X convention, the rendering of 形而上/形而下, the handling of the Laozi block quote — all of these have clear reasoning that will blur over the course of a full translation. A draft now captures the \"why\" while it's vivid. It also serves a practical function: a working Translator's Preface becomes a living reference document during translation, ensuring consistency as we move through later essays. We can and should revise it after translation is complete — add examples from later passages, adjust emphasis based on what proved most important — but the foundation should be laid now."
  }
